@abstract:
North-star contractile for IDApTIK, an asymmetric two-player infiltration
game. This file declares what the project WILL do next (tracked intents) and
what it WISHES to become (horizon aspirations), aligned to the vehicle-named
roadmap: Envelope -> Wheel -> Skateboard -> Bicycle -> Chassis -> Motorcycle
-> Computer Game.
@end

## Purpose

Ship an asymmetric infiltration game where the hacker solves a real, legible
network rather than pressing a "hack" button, and the infiltrator moves
through a physical space whose layer bites back. Rust owns gameplay truth;
Elixir owns multiplayer and session life.

## Anti-Purpose

IDApTIK is NOT:
- A shared-control co-op game (control is asymmetric by construction).
- A disembodied hacker-support role (the hacker has physical presence and risk).
- An engine-locked game (gameplay truth is engine-agnostic; frontends swap).
- A LiveView application (the session layer is Bandit + Phoenix Channels).

## If In Doubt

Ask before touching: the engine licence (AGPL-3.0-or-later), any docs/adr/
decision, the Rust<->Elixir wire format, or gameplay-truth determinism in
crates/idaptik-core.

## Committed Next-Actions

### envelope-playable-slice
- description: Core movement + basic hacker interactions (doors, elevators, overrides)
- probe: test -d crates/idaptik-core/src/scenario
- status: in_progress
- notes: Envelope (v0.1) minimum viable game (README "Roadmap").

### two-player-windowed-slice
- description: gossamer host window + burble transport two-player slice
- probe: grep -rq 'gossamer\|burble' docs/adr/0006-gossamer-host-and-burble-transport.md
- status: declared
- notes: ADR-0006.

### session-relay
- description: Elixir relay (Bandit + Phoenix Channels) over typed Command/Event
- probe: test -d server
- status: in_progress
- notes: ADR-0002, ADR-0005.

### config-schema-coverage
- description: Nickel schemas validate scenarios; negative fixtures fail config-check
- probe: test -f config/schema.ncl && test -d config/scenario-fixtures
- status: in_progress

## Wishes

